// TALKS

1.  Dan Steinman - Jaxcore Spin Introduction

Dan will demonstrate an innovative new IoT peripheral - the world's first wifi volume knob and dial remote control for that is fully programmable with JavaScript.

Dan is a long-time JavaScript enthusiast who's bringing his expertise to the world of web-connected hardware. [https://twitter.com/jaxcore](https://twitter.com/jaxcore)

2.  Branko Culum - PlinkoJS: Building an In-Browser Networked Physics Game in Javascript

PlinkoJS is a real-time, browser-based, multiplayer physics game. It was built using Javascript, [Node.js](http://Node.js), React, and WebSockets. PlinkoJS features a client-server architecture which synchronizes game state for multiple clients in real-time, allowing for real-time gameplay. This game features only technology native to the browser and does not depend on any special client-side plugins as most networked games do.

Branko Culum is a full-stack web developer who loves exploring how the web can be used to create real-time, collaborative experiences. [http://brankoculum.github.io/](http://brankoculum.github.io/)

3.  Third speaker wanted! Please email us at [team@torontojs.com](http://team@torontojs.com) if you would like to give a talk.

